pr_contents: As I’m sure you know, the hector_gazebo_sonar plugin is implemented using Gazebo’s ray sensor, which is essentially a laser scan. As a result, if the sensor’s beam hits the ground, it’s reflected back. I think sensors on the rover models were configured to scan horizontally for that reason, so the beams don’t hit the ground (there is no
configuration). I tried adding a vertical component to the scan myself and the results were sad.

It isn’t ideal to limit the sonar scans to a single horizontal plane, since the real world sensors have much larger fields of view. A block reflects the sonar if it’s held high enough in the claw, and a pile of blocks also reflects the sonar as the rover drives toward them. Neither of those things happen in the simulation.
It turns out that Gazebo actually has a sonar sensor, but until recently no one had written a ROS plugin to use it. However, there’s an open PR

that adds this functionality. Since it’s still open, has been for a few months, and seems to have lost traction in getting merged to the main branch, I suggest pulling the source to be built alongside our other Gazebo plugins.
This pull request brings in the sonar plugin and updates the rover models to use it.
Let me know what you think!

This is great. Unfortunately, I don't think we should merge it now since teams have probably written a lot of code, for better or worse, that rely on the current sensors behavior. It should definitely be used in future research.

I think this class in a ROS package does the 3D geometry stuff right, but like my CameraGeometry class, it only updates through TF which might be too slow for "real-time" reactions to our pitch and roll.

Here is my recommendation: fix CameraGeometry so that a user can change its orientation and/or pose, but continue to ignore the roll dimension in ProjectToWorld. pr_contents: リンクの色の設定箇所について、共通の処理を関数にまとめて整理しました。
If you use velodyne, set "scanner" to "velodyne" and set "use_velodyne" to "true".
If you use 3D URG, set "scanner" to "hokuyo" and set "use_velodyne" to "false".
GNSSドライバのディレクトリ構成を見直しました。
汎用的にGNSSドライバを起動するためのSerial GNSSを追加しました。
この変更によるビルドエラーは発生しておりません。
他に問題がなければマージおねがいします。
